Lizeka Tandwa, News24Simba Mhere (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; The trial of the man accused of killing Top Billing presenter Simba Mhere and his friend Kady-Shay O'Bryan was postponed in the Randburg Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Monday.Preshalin Naidoo&rsquo;s lawyer, Luando Voster, asked for a postponement as his colleague advocate Francois Roets had a stomach bug and would only be available on Tuesday.Roets is the advocate in charge of Naidoo's defence.Prosecutor Dinesh Nandkissor said he expected to conclude the State&rsquo;s case against Naidoo on Friday.During his brief appearance, Naidoo sat silently in the dock. He was dressed in a beige suit jacket and navy pants.Naidoo faces two counts of culpable homicide and additional charges of reckless or negligent driving, and inconsiderate driving. His VW Polo GTI crashed into Mhere&rsquo;s car on William Nicol Drive, Fourways, in the early hours of January 31, 2015.Mhere's father Joseph was a passenger in the car. He survived. O'Bryan had a three-year-old daughter.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.